.Dd 
.Dt BCOPY 3
.Os BSD 4.2
.Sh NAME
.Nm bcopy
.Nd copy byte string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <string.h>
.Ft void
.Fn bcopy "const void *src" "void *dst" "size_t len"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn bcopy
function
copies
.Fa len
bytes from string
.Fa src
to string
.Fa dst .
The two strings may overlap.
If
.Fa len
is zero, no bytes are copied.
